The best model that only uses the ending is the LSTM sequence model with ELMo embeddings , which obtains 43.6 % .
This model , as with most models studied , greatly improves with more context : by 3.1 % when given the initial noun phrase , and by an ad-ditional 4 % when also given the first sentence .

gained from.from sentence: Further improvement is gained from models that compute pairwise representations of the inputs .

simplest such model.from sentence: While the simplest such model , Dual - BoW , obtains only 35.1 % accuracy , combining In - fer Sent sentence representations gives 40.5 % accuracy ( InferSent - Bilinear ) .

pairwise NLI models.from sentence: The best results come from pairwise NLI models : when fully trained on Swag , ESIM + ELMo obtains 59.2 % accuracy .
